1
00:01:00,640 --> 00:01:01,280
Hello?

2
00:01:02,120 --> 00:01:02,680
Bro.

3
00:01:03,040 --> 00:01:04,040
Why aren't you here yet?

4
00:01:05,319 --> 00:01:06,120
Xiaofu.

5
00:01:07,080 --> 00:01:08,360
Something came up today.

6
00:01:08,840 --> 00:01:09,720
I can't make it.

7
00:01:11,120 --> 00:01:12,680
Tidy up the place for me.

8
00:01:14,120 --> 00:01:16,320
For Dahai and Guilan,

9
00:01:16,960 --> 00:01:17,920
burn some joss paper for me.

10
00:01:19,840 --> 00:01:22,160
I already burned some last night.

11
00:01:23,160 --> 00:01:23,760
Okay.

12
00:01:25,200 --> 00:01:26,000
Xiaofu.

13
00:01:27,640 --> 00:01:28,880
That thing...

14
00:01:31,280 --> 00:01:32,120
go ahead and burn it.

15
00:01:36,800 --> 00:01:38,720
Is everything okay on your end?

16
00:01:39,200 --> 00:01:40,280
I'm fine here.

17
00:01:41,400 --> 00:01:43,000
It's just some personal business.

18
00:01:44,040 --> 00:01:44,960
Are you sure?

19
00:01:47,400 --> 00:01:48,200
I'm sure.

20
00:01:51,160 --> 00:01:51,960
Burn it.

21
00:01:59,240 --> 00:02:00,040
Boss Wang.

22
00:02:01,640 --> 00:02:03,400
My men came to see you before,

23
00:02:04,160 --> 00:02:05,920
and you kicked them all out.

24
00:02:07,320 --> 00:02:08,800
This time I'm here in person.

25
00:02:09,960 --> 00:02:11,440
At least show some respect.

26
00:02:13,920 --> 00:02:14,800
Think it over.

27
00:03:01,680 --> 00:03:02,360
Bro,

28
00:03:02,360 --> 00:03:03,120
on this trip out there,

29
00:03:03,120 --> 00:03:04,520
we're gonna make big money, right?

30
00:03:04,520 --> 00:03:05,680
Absolutely.

31
00:03:06,280 --> 00:03:08,800
Bro has seen the big world out there.

32
00:03:09,080 --> 00:03:10,120
Stick with Bro and work hard,

33
00:03:10,120 --> 00:03:11,040
and you'll definitely make money.

34
00:03:12,240 --> 00:03:12,920
Bro,

35
00:03:12,920 --> 00:03:15,280
the two of us aren't after riches.

36
00:03:15,520 --> 00:03:17,200
We just want our kid, someday,

37
00:03:17,280 --> 00:03:19,280
to live in a house we built ourselves,

38
00:03:19,320 --> 00:03:20,760
in a nice place. That's all.

39
00:03:20,760 --> 00:03:21,280
Right?

40
00:03:21,480 --> 00:03:22,880
Don't worry, Dahai.

41
00:03:23,120 --> 00:03:24,640
For sure, for sure.

42
00:03:24,640 --> 00:03:25,480
Yeah, Dahai.

43
00:03:25,560 --> 00:03:26,720
We'll just follow Bro's lead.

44
00:03:26,720 --> 00:03:28,320
For sure, for sure.

45
00:03:28,320 --> 00:03:29,480
Yeah, for sure.

46
00:03:29,720 --> 00:03:30,560
Roll with Bro,

47
00:03:30,560 --> 00:03:31,320
and don't you worry.

48
00:03:31,320 --> 00:03:32,720
Bro has seen the world.

49
00:03:32,720 --> 00:03:33,640
Out there, it's all money.

50
00:03:33,640 --> 00:03:34,360
Brother,

51
00:03:34,360 --> 00:03:35,040
that's our bro for you.

52
00:03:35,040 --> 00:03:36,200
You just bend down and pick it up.

53
00:03:36,200 --> 00:03:37,720
More than you can even grab.

54
00:03:37,840 --> 00:03:39,440
Stick with bro, and the money will flow.

55
00:04:03,840 --> 00:04:04,720
Hello, sir.

56
00:04:04,880 --> 00:04:06,160
I'd like to ask you something.

57
00:04:06,160 --> 00:04:07,240
In this village,

58
00:04:07,240 --> 00:04:08,880
is there anyone named Liu Guilan?

59
00:04:10,880 --> 00:04:12,000
Doesn't ring a bell.

60
00:04:12,320 --> 00:04:14,120
Everyone in this village is surnamed Wang.

61
00:04:14,800 --> 00:04:15,960
No one named Liu.

62
00:04:16,480 --> 00:04:17,720
Try asking someone else.

63
00:04:18,240 --> 00:04:18,760
Okay.

64
00:04:18,760 --> 00:04:19,920
Thanks. Sorry to bother you.

65
00:04:24,600 --> 00:04:25,040
Sir.

66
00:04:25,040 --> 00:04:26,160
I'd like to ask about someone.

67
00:04:26,200 --> 00:04:26,800
Go ahead.

68
00:04:26,800 --> 00:04:28,360
Do you know someone named Liu Guilan?

69
00:04:28,600 --> 00:04:29,840
Never heard of her.

70
00:04:30,360 --> 00:04:31,440
What's this about?

71
00:04:32,400 --> 00:04:32,960
Nothing.

72
00:04:32,960 --> 00:04:33,720
Thanks anyway.

73
00:04:33,920 --> 00:04:35,640
If you need anything, ask the village chief.

74
00:04:35,880 --> 00:04:36,440
Okay.

75
00:04:40,880 --> 00:04:41,880
That's strange.

76
00:04:42,320 --> 00:04:43,720
I've asked several people along the way,

77
00:04:43,720 --> 00:04:44,840
and no one knows her.

78
00:04:45,320 --> 00:04:47,640
Could they be misremembering?

79
00:04:48,160 --> 00:04:50,560
That old guy I just asked said the same.

80
00:04:50,680 --> 00:04:52,840
Didn't he say to ask the village chief?

81
00:04:53,560 --> 00:04:55,640
Then let's go ask at the village committee.

82
00:04:59,000 --> 00:04:59,720
Let's go then.

83
00:04:59,720 --> 00:05:00,160
Come on.

84
00:05:33,160 --> 00:05:34,440
We'd better hurry.

85
00:05:35,280 --> 00:05:36,760
I'm worried those three kids

86
00:05:37,440 --> 00:05:38,440
might wander over

87
00:05:38,440 --> 00:05:40,200
to Zhou Dahai's place any minute now.

88
00:06:03,680 --> 00:06:05,160
Lucky Village, Number 28.

89
00:06:05,280 --> 00:06:07,000
First little red house on the right.

90
00:06:08,120 --> 00:06:09,320
Go give them a hand.

91
00:06:13,880 --> 00:06:14,680
Hey, you guys.

92
00:06:14,800 --> 00:06:15,600
What are you doing here?

93
00:06:21,560 --> 00:06:23,520
We came to the village to ask

94
00:06:23,520 --> 00:06:25,360
if there's someone named Liu Guilan.

95
00:06:25,480 --> 00:06:26,360
Liu Guilan?

96
00:06:27,880 --> 00:06:28,680
Let me think.

97
00:06:29,160 --> 00:06:30,400
Liu Guilan...

98
00:06:31,760 --> 00:06:32,560
Or else,

99
00:06:32,560 --> 00:06:34,480
do you know where the village chief lives?

100
00:06:35,440 --> 00:06:36,880
That name sounds

101
00:06:36,960 --> 00:06:37,960
really familiar.

102
00:06:38,520 --> 00:06:39,280
Let me think...

103
00:06:42,240 --> 00:06:43,600
You know what, I actually remember now.

104
00:06:43,600 --> 00:06:44,440
Over a decade ago,

105
00:06:44,560 --> 00:06:46,000
there was an outsider couple

106
00:06:46,000 --> 00:06:46,960
on the east end of the village.

107
00:06:47,320 --> 00:06:48,120
But,

108
00:06:48,600 --> 00:06:50,320
I think they died over ten years ago.

109
00:06:50,600 --> 00:06:51,840
What do you want with her?

110
00:06:53,560 --> 00:06:54,640
They're dead?

111
00:06:54,960 --> 00:06:55,760
Are you sure?

112
00:06:56,280 --> 00:06:57,280
I'm sure.

113
00:06:57,360 --> 00:06:58,400
I was just a kid back then.

114
00:06:58,400 --> 00:06:59,480
I used to play at their place all the time.

115
00:06:59,720 --> 00:07:00,440
Then one year,

116
00:07:00,440 --> 00:07:01,480
they said they were going to the city,

117
00:07:01,480 --> 00:07:02,520
and never came back.

118
00:07:04,120 --> 00:07:06,560
I heard they had a kid when they left.

119
00:07:13,400 --> 00:07:15,560
Could you take us to their house?

120
00:07:16,200 --> 00:07:16,680
Sure.

121
00:07:16,720 --> 00:07:17,680
Follow me.

122
00:07:45,200 --> 00:07:46,080
Boss Wang.

123
00:07:46,840 --> 00:07:47,880
Think faster.

124
00:07:48,920 --> 00:07:50,400
Once that door is pushed open,

125
00:07:51,120 --> 00:07:52,080
that child...

126
00:07:53,000 --> 00:07:54,560
I'm afraid he won't be able to take it.

127
00:08:07,880 --> 00:08:11,640
What's their connection to Lucky Village?

128
00:08:13,640 --> 00:08:15,160
Even though I hate to part with it,

129
00:08:15,880 --> 00:08:17,160
once this job is done,

130
00:08:17,640 --> 00:08:18,800
it'll be time to say goodbye.

131
00:08:20,280 --> 00:08:22,880
With the money, I'll surprise old Wang.

132
00:08:29,200 --> 00:08:30,000
Boss Wu.

133
00:08:30,720 --> 00:08:32,559
I've got people in my village too.

134
00:08:33,799 --> 00:08:35,440
Don't push me too far.

135
00:08:43,200 --> 00:08:44,000
People?

136
00:08:46,480 --> 00:08:47,560
That cripple?

137
00:08:50,280 --> 00:08:52,040
You think he can stop me?

138
00:09:05,720 --> 00:09:06,600
This is the place.

139
00:09:06,760 --> 00:09:08,000
This is Liu Guilan's house.

140
00:09:14,200 --> 00:09:15,360
This is Liu Guilan's house.

141
00:09:16,320 --> 00:09:16,880
Perfect timing.

142
00:09:16,880 --> 00:09:18,000
The village chief is here too.

143
00:09:18,640 --> 00:09:20,480
Didn't you want to ask him something?

144
00:09:23,720 --> 00:09:24,760
What do you want?

145
00:09:26,200 --> 00:09:27,480
Hello, Chief.

146
00:09:27,480 --> 00:09:28,680
We came here looking for

147
00:09:28,680 --> 00:09:29,880
information about Liu Guilan.

148
00:09:30,040 --> 00:09:31,640
We heard before she moved to the city,

149
00:09:31,640 --> 00:09:33,120
she used to live around here.

150
00:09:34,120 --> 00:09:34,960
There's no such person.

151
00:09:35,440 --> 00:09:36,400
You'd better leave now.

152
00:09:36,400 --> 00:09:38,480
Wasn't there supposed to be a child too?

153
00:09:39,960 --> 00:09:40,760
Uncle Wang Fu,

154
00:09:41,280 --> 00:09:42,240
that's not right.

155
00:09:42,960 --> 00:09:44,800
I remember Liu Guilan lived here.

156
00:09:45,000 --> 00:09:46,600
I used to play here as a kid.

157
00:09:47,120 --> 00:09:48,200
What do you know?

158
00:09:48,200 --> 00:09:48,960
Get lost, now.

159
00:09:49,400 --> 00:09:51,000
How many years has it been?

160
00:09:51,440 --> 00:09:52,760
Back when you caused trouble here,

161
00:09:53,040 --> 00:09:55,160
we spared you for your grandpa's sake.

162
00:09:55,640 --> 00:09:56,800
If you keep spouting nonsense,

163
00:09:57,160 --> 00:09:58,720
I won't be so nice anymore.

164
00:09:59,760 --> 00:10:00,640
And as for you lot,

165
00:10:01,200 --> 00:10:02,400
the person you're looking for isn't here.

166
00:10:03,200 --> 00:10:03,800
Get out, now.

167
00:10:08,560 --> 00:10:09,640
You old bastard.

168
00:10:09,960 --> 00:10:11,360
If I show you respect,

169
00:10:11,440 --> 00:10:12,520
I'll call you Uncle.

170
00:10:12,800 --> 00:10:13,760
If I don't,

171
00:10:13,760 --> 00:10:14,920
I'll tear your house down.

172
00:10:14,960 --> 00:10:16,000
Beat me to death?

173
00:10:16,120 --> 00:10:16,840
Who the hell do you think you are?

174
00:10:16,840 --> 00:10:17,480
No, no, no.

175
00:10:17,480 --> 00:10:17,880
There's no need for this.

176
00:10:17,880 --> 00:10:18,440
Move.

177
00:10:19,520 --> 00:10:20,320
Zhou Yi.

178
00:10:20,880 --> 00:10:21,920
Zhou Yi, are you okay?

179
00:10:22,440 --> 00:10:23,240
How is it?

180
00:10:23,360 --> 00:10:24,080
You alright?

181
00:10:25,000 --> 00:10:25,880
Are you okay?

182
00:10:26,320 --> 00:10:26,960
I'm fine.

183
00:10:26,960 --> 00:10:27,680
Just give me a moment.

184
00:10:27,840 --> 00:10:28,640
A moment, just a moment.

185
00:10:28,800 --> 00:10:30,240
If you lay hands on an old man again,

186
00:10:30,240 --> 00:10:31,520
and keep running that filthy mouth,

187
00:10:31,520 --> 00:10:32,840
watch out, I won't be polite either.

188
00:10:33,240 --> 00:10:34,800
Now you're flipping it on me?

189
00:10:36,240 --> 00:10:37,240
You little punk,

190
00:10:37,560 --> 00:10:39,000
you don't look like a decent guy.

191
00:10:39,400 --> 00:10:41,400
And now you're putting on airs with me?

192
00:10:45,240 --> 00:10:47,360
Hey, can you speak nicely or not?

193
00:10:47,680 --> 00:10:49,200
We only let you lead the way

194
00:10:49,200 --> 00:10:50,440
thinking you were a decent guy.

195
00:10:50,600 --> 00:10:52,120
If you talk to my friend like that again,

196
00:10:52,360 --> 00:10:53,960
we'll have to handle this differently.

197
00:10:54,680 --> 00:10:55,840
Unbelievable.

198
00:10:55,840 --> 00:10:56,560
Little girl,

199
00:10:56,560 --> 00:10:58,040
do you know what this old man is like?

200
00:10:58,280 --> 00:10:59,480
Listen here, old man,

201
00:10:59,560 --> 00:11:01,360
Don't think your dirty secrets are hidden.

202
00:11:01,880 --> 00:11:03,640
Today, I'm going in to take a look.

203
00:11:04,040 --> 00:11:05,320
I'll let the whole village know

204
00:11:05,320 --> 00:11:06,880
Liu Guilan's family lived right here.

205
00:11:06,880 --> 00:11:08,640
Her husband was named Zhou Dahai.

206
00:11:08,720 --> 00:11:10,160
And there was a child too.

207
00:11:10,160 --> 00:11:10,920
Shut up!

208
00:11:12,160 --> 00:11:13,160
You want to see the house, right?

209
00:11:14,520 --> 00:11:15,040
Fine.

210
00:11:18,840 --> 00:11:19,920
I'll let you in.

211
00:11:20,720 --> 00:11:21,600
But get lost as soon as you're done.

212
00:11:44,080 --> 00:11:44,600
Lin You.

213
00:11:58,200 --> 00:11:59,000
Wait a minute.

214
00:12:00,600 --> 00:12:01,280
What is it?

215
00:12:02,880 --> 00:12:03,680
Master said

216
00:12:04,080 --> 00:12:05,960
he's at Daji, told us to hurry back.

217
00:12:06,960 --> 00:12:08,120
We're already here.

218
00:12:08,120 --> 00:12:09,440
Why worry about that now?

219
00:12:10,920 --> 00:12:12,560
Master sold Daji.

220
00:12:14,560 --> 00:12:15,360
What?

221
00:12:31,520 --> 00:12:32,320
Why?

222
00:12:32,640 --> 00:12:33,800
Why is he selling Daji?

223
00:12:36,720 --> 00:12:37,520
Stop yelling.

224
00:12:40,920 --> 00:12:41,960
This place...

225
00:12:42,800 --> 00:12:44,280
I've wanted to sell it for ages.

226
00:12:46,360 --> 00:12:47,600
All this spooky nonsense.

227
00:12:47,600 --> 00:12:48,640
I'm tired of it too.

228
00:12:49,840 --> 00:12:51,480
How many times have I told you?

229
00:12:51,840 --> 00:12:53,320
Stay out of Daji's business.

230
00:12:53,320 --> 00:12:54,720
Stay out of Daji's business!

231
00:12:54,840 --> 00:12:56,440
Why won't you ever listen?

232
00:13:08,080 --> 00:13:09,400
Just buy the shop back.

233
00:13:10,120 --> 00:13:12,200
I'll never set foot in Daji again.

234
00:13:12,440 --> 00:13:13,240
Okay?

235
00:13:16,280 --> 00:13:17,080
Uncle Wang.

236
00:13:17,280 --> 00:13:18,080
Enough.

237
00:13:18,880 --> 00:13:19,680
Stop talking.

238
00:13:20,360 --> 00:13:21,640
This is my own shop.

239
00:13:22,480 --> 00:13:23,280
Whether I sell it or not,

240
00:13:23,520 --> 00:13:24,720
is none of your business.

241
00:13:39,280 --> 00:13:40,160
Who did you sell it to?

242
00:13:42,920 --> 00:13:43,960
Just start packing up.

243
00:13:44,360 --> 00:13:45,720
You've only got one month.

244
00:14:31,080 --> 00:14:31,840
Sir, who are you here to see?

245
00:14:34,880 --> 00:14:35,680
You can't go in.

246
00:14:36,080 --> 00:14:36,880
Brother You.

247
00:14:51,360 --> 00:14:52,160
Where's the contract?

248
00:14:52,320 --> 00:14:53,480
Take it out. Tear it up.

249
00:15:00,840 --> 00:15:01,640
Well, well.

250
00:15:03,080 --> 00:15:03,960
You've grown up.

251
00:15:05,440 --> 00:15:07,360
Boss Wang signed it willingly.

252
00:15:07,600 --> 00:15:08,560
What good would tearing it up do?

253
00:15:16,840 --> 00:15:17,560
Look around.

254
00:15:19,360 --> 00:15:21,400
This is everything I have now.

255
00:15:23,080 --> 00:15:25,000
Back in that little shack,

256
00:15:25,000 --> 00:15:25,960
everything I promised you,

257
00:15:26,640 --> 00:15:27,640
I've made it all happen.

258
00:15:28,560 --> 00:15:30,120
And it's all ready.

259
00:15:30,120 --> 00:15:31,280
All you have to do is come back,

260
00:15:33,120 --> 00:15:33,920
little brother.

261
00:15:34,840 --> 00:15:36,240
We're already living

262
00:15:36,240 --> 00:15:37,640
in that high-rise across the street.

263
00:15:39,240 --> 00:15:40,560
Whether it was willing or not,

264
00:15:41,080 --> 00:15:42,480
you know damn well.

265
00:15:43,240 --> 00:15:44,920
Was the abandoned building your doing too?

266
00:15:47,560 --> 00:15:48,600
It cost a bit of money,

267
00:15:49,800 --> 00:15:50,720
but it was worth it.

268
00:15:51,440 --> 00:15:52,080
Wasn't it?

269
00:15:54,440 --> 00:15:56,400
What you do over there is just

270
00:15:56,600 --> 00:15:58,000
a bunch of mumbo-jumbo, isn't it?

271
00:15:59,080 --> 00:16:00,040
How was my little stunt?

272
00:16:00,720 --> 00:16:02,120
Times have changed.

273
00:16:02,440 --> 00:16:03,800
Even if you're going to fool people,

274
00:16:04,000 --> 00:16:05,480
you've got to do it properly.

275
00:16:08,200 --> 00:16:09,280
You did all this

276
00:16:10,400 --> 00:16:12,560
just for a childhood joke?

277
00:16:16,240 --> 00:16:17,080
A joke?

278
00:16:25,320 --> 00:16:25,960
Maybe so.

279
00:16:27,720 --> 00:16:28,680
At least that joke

280
00:16:28,680 --> 00:16:30,440
gave me everything I have now.

281
00:16:32,120 --> 00:16:34,040
But do you really have to use such methods

282
00:16:34,280 --> 00:16:36,200
to get what you want?

283
00:16:37,200 --> 00:16:38,520
Do you know you're hurting

284
00:16:38,520 --> 00:16:39,840
the closest family I have?

285
00:16:46,080 --> 00:16:47,680
The day I got out, I told you,

286
00:16:48,080 --> 00:16:49,800
I don't want that kind of life anymore.

287
00:16:49,800 --> 00:16:51,680
I finally have a life like this,

288
00:16:51,680 --> 00:16:52,320
but what about you?

289
00:16:52,320 --> 00:16:54,240
The truth isn't what you think at all.

290
00:16:57,480 --> 00:16:58,320
Lin You,

291
00:16:59,640 --> 00:17:01,040
no matter where you go,

292
00:17:01,680 --> 00:17:03,480
once they know you've done time,

293
00:17:03,480 --> 00:17:05,280
they'll look at you differently.

294
00:17:06,480 --> 00:17:08,200
You want a normal life,

295
00:17:08,720 --> 00:17:10,119
but people like us,

296
00:17:10,280 --> 00:17:12,520
we have nowhere to live a normal life.

297
00:17:18,400 --> 00:17:20,160
Only we are family.

298
00:17:21,680 --> 00:17:24,359
You know how filthy this world is.

299
00:17:26,520 --> 00:17:27,599
Do you really want to go back

300
00:17:27,599 --> 00:17:29,120
to that place from our childhood?

301
00:17:30,000 --> 00:17:31,120
Curled up there,

302
00:17:31,880 --> 00:17:32,920
at everyone's mercy?

303
00:17:47,160 --> 00:17:48,400
I used to think

304
00:17:48,920 --> 00:17:50,200
I should accept my fate.

305
00:17:52,080 --> 00:17:54,160
But now I've found that place,

306
00:17:55,480 --> 00:17:57,760
and you want to destroy it yourself.

307
00:18:09,000 --> 00:18:10,200
Daji is my home.

308
00:18:11,240 --> 00:18:12,040
You've got nerve.

309
00:18:12,480 --> 00:18:14,520
Then bury me within your empire.

310
00:18:15,320 --> 00:18:16,480
As long as I'm here,

311
00:18:17,400 --> 00:18:18,960
you can't touch Daji.

312
00:18:21,400 --> 00:18:22,040
Fine.

313
00:18:23,800 --> 00:18:25,920
From now on, what you do at Daji,

314
00:18:26,440 --> 00:18:27,560
I won't interfere with.

315
00:18:29,320 --> 00:18:30,640
You'll see for yourself

316
00:18:30,640 --> 00:18:32,560
what kind of people they really are.
